                <summary>The friends of the Valley Railroad held a meeting in Moscow. Jacob
                    Shreckhise served as chair and P. Herring as secretary. Committees were
                    appointed to solicit subscriptions to the road. The meeting demanded, however,
                    that the road be built via Bridgewater and Long Glade.</summary>
